---
export const prerender = true;

import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../../consts';
---

<ServiceLayout
	title={`Networking Infrastructure | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
	description="Secure, distributed networks for personal use—whether you seek managed simplicity or self-hosted control."
>
	<h1>Networking Infrastructure</h1>
	<p class="intro">
		Secure, distributed networks for personal use—whether you seek managed simplicity or self-hosted control.
	</p>

	<section class="overview">
		<h2>What This Offers</h2>
		<p>
			Modern networking doesn't have to be complex. Whether you're connecting your home lab,
			securing remote access to your personal servers, or building a private mesh network for
			friends and family—the right solution depends on your comfort level and requirements.
		</p>
		<p>
			Both approaches below run on <strong>WireGuard</strong>—modern, fast, and battle-tested
			cryptography. The difference is who manages the infrastructure.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="approaches">
		<h2>Two Approaches</h2>

		<div class="approach-card managed">
			<div class="approach-icon">
				<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" width="48" height="48">
					<path d="M12 6a6 6 0 1 0 0 12 6 6 0 0 0 0-12Zm0 10a4 4 0 1 1 0-8 4 4 0 0 1 0 8Zm6-10a2 2 0 1 0 0 4 2 2 0 0 0 0-4Zm0 4.5a.5.5 0 1 1 0-1 .5.5 0 0 1 0 1ZM6 4a2 2 0 1 0 0 4 2 2 0 0 0 0-4Zm0 4.5a.5.5 0 1 1 0-1 .5.5 0 0 1 0 1Zm12 7a2 2 0 1 0 0 4 2 2 0 0 0 0-4Zm0 4.5a.5.5 0 1 1 0-1 .5.5 0 0 1 0 1ZM6 13a2 2 0 1 0 0 4 2 2 0 0 0 0-4Zm0 4.5a.5.5 0 1 1 0-1 .5.5 0 0 1 0 1ZM21 12a3 3 0 1 1-6 0 3 3 0 0 1 6 0Zm0-9a3 3 0 1 1-6 0 3 3 0 0 1 6 0Zm0 18a3 3 0 1 1-6 0 3 3 0 0 1 6 0ZM3 12a3 3 0 1 1-6 0 3 3 0 0 1 6 0Zm0-9a3 3 0 1 1-6 0 3 3 0 0 1 6 0Zm0 18a3 3 0 1 1-6 0 3 3 0 0 1 6 0Z"/>
				</svg>
			</div>
			<div class="approach-content">
				<div class="approach-header">
					<h3>Zero-Config Simplicity</h3>
					<span class="approach-badge">Managed</span>
				</div>
				<p>
					Let Tailscale handle the infrastructure. Get a secure WireGuard mesh network
					up and running in minutes with SSO integration, MagicDNS, and automatic NAT traversal.
				</p>
				<ul class="approach-features">
					<li>Works with GitHub, Google, Okta, Microsoft</li>
					<li>No firewall rules to configure</li>
					<li>Automatic key rotation</li>
					<li>Great for small to medium teams</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="approach-card self-hosted">
			<div class="approach-icon">
				<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" width="48" height="48">
					<rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="6" rx="2"/>
					<rect x="2" y="15" width="20" height="6" rx="2"/>
					<path d="M6 6h.01M6 18h.01M12 6h.01M12 18h.01M18 6h.01M18 18h.01"/>
				</svg>
			</div>
			<div class="approach-content">
				<div class="approach-header">
					<h3>Own Your Infrastructure</h3>
					<span class="approach-badge">Self-Hosted</span>
				</div>
				<p>
					Deploy NetBird or custom WireGuard on your own servers. Full control over
					data, authentication, and network topology. Perfect for security-conscious
					users and specific compliance requirements.
				</p>
				<ul class="approach-features">
					<li>Data never leaves your infrastructure</li>
					<li>Custom identity providers</li>
					<li>Air-gapped network support</li>
					<li>Audit logging & compliance</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="ideal-for">
		<h2>Ideal For</h2>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Home Lab Connectivity:</strong> Securely access your servers from anywhere</li>
			<li><strong>Remote Access:</strong> Connect to your home network while traveling</li>
			<li><strong>Secure Browsing:</strong> Route traffic through your own infrastructure</li>
			<li><strong>Friend & Family Networks:</strong> Share services privately with trusted circles</li>
			<li><strong>Development Environments:</strong> Seamless connections between local and cloud resources</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</ServiceLayout>

<style>
	/* Override centered intro — networking has no header-section */
	.intro {
		text-align: left;
	}

	.approaches {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 1.5rem;
	}

	.approach-card {
		background: var(--bg-color);
		border: 2px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
		border-radius: 16px;
		padding: 2rem;
		display: flex;
		gap: 1.5rem;
		transition: all 0.3s ease;
	}

	.approach-card:hover {
		border-color: var(--accent);
		transform: translateY(-4px);
		box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
	}

	.approach-icon {
		color: var(--accent);
		flex-shrink: 0;
	}

	.approach-card.self-hosted .approach-icon {
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
	}

	.approach-content {
		flex: 1;
	}

	.approach-header {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		align-items: center;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		gap: 0.5rem;
	}

	.approach-header h3 {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		margin: 0;
		color: var(--heading-color);
	}

	.approach-badge {
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem;
		background: rgb(var(--gray-light));
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		border-radius: 20px;
		white-space: nowrap;
	}

	.approach-content > p {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.approach-features {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}

	.approach-features li {
		padding: 0.35rem 0;
		padding-left: 1.25rem;
		position: relative;
	}

	.approach-features li::before {
		content: "✓";
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		color: var(--accent);
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.approach-card {
			flex-direction: column;
		}

		.approach-header {
			flex-direction: column;
			align-items: flex-start;
		}
	}
</style>
